Q - Binary tree maximum path sum leetcode 124
Ans -  Approch we use DFS using recursive function to solve , first we check left and right if -ve we make whloe side of left and right -ve 
then we find maxi , adding node.val ,left,right and compare with maxi whiche is -inf by default then update maxi .
next find max Left and right and add to maxi. and return.
TC - O(n)
SC - O(H) - height {stack space}

# Definition for a binary tree node.
# class TreeNode(object):
#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):
#         self.val = val
#         self.left = left
#         self.right = right
class Solution(object):
    def maxPathSum(self, root):
        self.maxi = float('-inf')
        """
        :type root: Optional[TreeNode]
        :rtype: int
        """-
